!! Civilian Pursuits
"No soldier gets entangled in civilian pursuits, since his aim is to please the one who enlisted him."

"Civilian pursuits" mean might be known as "worldly desires or pursuits."

!! Athletes
Athletes are disciplined. We are a perfect picture of discipline. I don't think that this is what Paul is emphasizing here.

!! Hard Workers
"It is the hard-working farmer who ought to have the first share of the crops."
Here we see the need for hard-working in order to be reminded of our reward.

There is an inheritance that is imperishable and undefiled.